4.description: Dataset contains polygons that represent the Proposed FEMA Floodway(0.1). The floodway is an area that must be reserved in order to discharge of the 100 year flood without cumulatively increasing the water surface elevation more than 0.1 feet. No fill or construction is permitted in this area
4.title: Meck Flood Zones

5.description: The dataset contains the utility right-of-ways for the county digitized from data compiled from county manual tax maps onto planimetric maps. The name of the utility company owning the right-of-way is part of the dataset.
5.title: Meck Utility

6.description: This dataset contains all the rail lines in the county and is based on the county's street centerline file. The county in description is Mecklenburg County, North Carolina.
6.title: Meck Railroads

7.description: MAPFLDHAZAR is a polygon feature class representing the area within the flood mapping boundaries defined by the engineering models for the 100 year, 500 year and floodway. The MapFldHazAr spatial table contains information about the flood hazard within the study area. These zones are used by FEMA to designate the Special Flood Hazard Area (SFHA), identify areas of coastal high hazard flooding, and for insurance rating purposes. These data are the flood hazard areas that are or will be depicted on the FIRM.
7.title: Union Flood Zones
